{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_25","type":"agent_message","text":"Clone verification succeeded. The decoded rule is: symbol `0` means “match this clue’s center state,” symbol `2` means “take the opposite state,” and the lone cell with no clue is a true don’t-care. Solving the observed action matrix produces a 21-click winning prefix; the inverse interpretation reaches all 30 cells of the wrong pattern and earns no reward. I’ll now package that as one reusable coupled-toggle planner and keep `play_level_5` as a one-line composition."}}
